===Etymology===
STEDT compared this to {{cog|bo|བྲེད་པ་||to be alarmed, scared}}. If the relation is to be established, then this term is derived from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*b-ray-t||fear}}.

Hong Kong Cantonese {{m-g|to be scared}} is borrowed from {{bor|yue|zhx-tai|慄|tr=nut{{sup|5}}}}.

